[Kufra (Al-Kufrah), in the Kufra district, south eastern Libya, is an oasis situated in the middle of the Sahara desert. A map can be found at: http://www.fallingrain.com/world/LY/08/Al_Kufrah.html.

Confirmation or otherwise would be requested. If confirmed, the identity of the FMDV serotype would be appreciated.

Libya suffered outbreaks of FMDV serotypes SAT2 and O earlier this year (2012). Their respective genotyping results are available at http://www.wrlfmd.org/fmd_genotyping/africa/lib.htm.

For an overview of the events earlier in 2012, see commentary in archived post 20120509.1127864. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1_fL.]
